2229  }
2230  else if (inOutNumPixels == 3840)

2285 
2286 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::canDrawTestPattern (const NTV2TestPatternSelect inPattern, const NTV2FormatDescriptor & inDesc)
2287 {
2288  if (!inDesc.IsValid())
2289  return false; // Format descriptor must be valid
2290  if (NTV2_IS_12B_PATTERN(inPattern))
2291  {
2292  if (inDesc.GetRasterWidth() % 1920)
2293  return false; // Pixel width must be evenly divisible by 1920
2294  if (inDesc.GetPixelFormat() != NTV2_FBF_48BIT_RGB) //&& inDesc.GetPixelFormat() != NTV2_FBF_12BIT_RGB_PACKED)
2295  return false; // Pixel format must be RGB-12b
2296  return true;
2297  }
2298  return NTV2_IS_VALID_PATTERN(inPattern);
2299 }

2318 
2325 static const size_t sNumPatterns(sizeof(NTV2TestPatternSegments)/sizeof(SegmentTestPatternData));
2326 
2327 static TPStringMap & CreateTPStringMap (TPStringMap & outMap)
2328 {
2329  if (!outMap.empty())
2330  return outMap;
2331  NTV2_ASSERT(sNumPatterns == NTV2_TestPatt_Black);
2332  for (NTV2TestPatternSelect tpSelect(NTV2_TestPatt_FIRST); tpSelect < sNumPatterns; tpSelect = NTV2TestPatternSelect(tpSelect+1))
2333  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(tpSelect, string(NTV2TestPatternSegments[tpSelect].name)));
2334  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_Black, string("Black")));
2335  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_White, string("White")));
2336  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_Border, string("Border")));
2337  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_LinearRamp, string("Linear Ramp")));
2338  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_SlantRamp, string("Slant Ramp")));
2339  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_ZonePlate, string("Zone Plate")));
2340  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_ColorQuadrant, string("Color Quadrant")));
2341  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_ColorQuadrantBorder, string("Color Quadrant Border")));
2342  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_ColorQuadrantTsi, string("Color Quadrant Tsi")));
2343  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_TsiAlignment, string("Color Quadrant Tsi2")));
2344  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_ZonePlate_12b_RGB, string("ZonePlate 12b RGB")));
2345  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_LinearRamp_12b_RGB, string("LinearRamp 12b RGB")));
2346  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_HLG_Narrow_12b_RGB, string("HLG_Narrow 12b RGB")));
2347  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_PQ_Narrow_12b_RGB, string("PQ_Narrow 12b RGB")));
2348  outMap.insert(TPStringPair(NTV2_TestPatt_PQ_Wide_12b_RGB, string("PQ_Wide 12b RGB")));
2349  return outMap;
2350 }
2351 
2352 static StringTPMap & CreateStringTPMap (StringTPMap & outMap)
2353 {
2354  if (!outMap.empty())
2355  return outMap;
2356 
2357  TPStringMap TPNames;
2358  ::CreateTPStringMap(TPNames);
2359  // Invert the TPStringMap...
2360  for (TPStringMapConstIter it(TPNames.begin()); it != TPNames.end(); ++it)
2361  { string name(it->second);
2362  outMap[aja::lower(name)] = it->first;
2363  if (name.find(' ') != string::npos)
2364  aja::replace(name, " ", "");
2365  if (name.find('%') != string::npos)
2366  aja::replace(name, "%", "");
2367  if (outMap.find(name) == outMap.end())
2368  outMap[name] = it->first;
2369  }
2370  return outMap;
2371 }

2521 static StringRGBMap & CreateStringRGBMap (StringRGBMap & outMap)
2522 {
2523  if (!outMap.empty())
2524  return outMap;
2525  RGBStringMap webColors;
2526  ::CreateRGBStringMap(webColors);
2527  // Invert webColors...
2528  for (RGBStringMapConstIter it(webColors.begin()); it != webColors.end(); ++it)
2529  { string name(it->second);
2530  outMap[aja::lower(name)] = it->first;
2531  }
2532  outMap["darkgrey"] = 0x00A9A9A9;
2533  outMap["darkslategrey"] = 0x002F4F4F;
2534  outMap["dimgrey"] = 0x00696969;
2535  outMap["grey"] = 0x00808080;
2536  outMap["lightgrey"] = 0x00D3D3D3;
2537  outMap["lightslategrey"] = 0x00778899;
2538  outMap["slategrey"] = 0x00708090;
2539  return outMap;
2540 }

2552 NTV2StringList NTV2TestPatternGen::getColorNames (void)
2553 {
2554  NTV2StringList result;
2555  RGBStringMap rgbStringMap;
2556  StringRGBMap strToWebColors;
2557  ::CreateRGBStringMap(rgbStringMap);
2558  ::CreateStringRGBMap(strToWebColors);
2559  // Accumulate mixed-case names...
2560  for (StringRGBMapConstIter iter(strToWebColors.begin()); iter != strToWebColors.end(); ++iter)
2561  { RGBStringMapConstIter it(rgbStringMap.find(findRGBColorByName(iter->first)));
2562  if (it != rgbStringMap.end())
2563  result.push_back(it->second);
2564  }
2565  return result;
2566 }

2616 
2617 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::drawIt (void)
2618 {
2619  bool result(false);
2620  switch (mPatternID)
2621  {
2622  case NTV2_TestPatt_ColorBars100:
2623  case NTV2_TestPatt_ColorBars75:
2624  case NTV2_TestPatt_Ramp:
2625  case NTV2_TestPatt_MultiBurst:
2626  case NTV2_TestPatt_LineSweep:
2627  case NTV2_TestPatt_CheckField:
2628  case NTV2_TestPatt_FlatField:
2629  case NTV2_TestPatt_MultiPattern:
2630  result = DrawSegmentedTestPattern();
2631  break;
2632 
2633  case NTV2_TestPatt_Black:
2634  result = DrawYCbCrFrame(CCIR601_10BIT_BLACK,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET);
2635  break;
2636  case NTV2_TestPatt_White:
2637  result = DrawYCbCrFrame(CCIR601_10BIT_WHITE,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET);
2638  break;
2639 
2640  case NTV2_TestPatt_Border: result = DrawBorderFrame(); break;
2641  case NTV2_TestPatt_SlantRamp: result = DrawSlantRampFrame(); break;
2642  case NTV2_TestPatt_ZonePlate: result = DrawZonePlateFrame(); break;
2643  case NTV2_TestPatt_ColorQuadrant: result = DrawColorQuadrantFrame(); break;
2644  case NTV2_TestPatt_ColorQuadrantBorder: result = DrawQuadrantBorderFrame(); break;
2645  case NTV2_TestPatt_LinearRamp: result = DrawLinearRampFrame(); break;
2646  case NTV2_TestPatt_ColorQuadrantTsi: result = DrawColorQuadrantFrameTsi(); break;
2647  case NTV2_TestPatt_TsiAlignment: result = DrawColorQuadrantFrameTsi2(); break;
2648  case NTV2_TestPatt_ZonePlate_12b_RGB: result = Draw12BitZonePlate(); break;
2649  case NTV2_TestPatt_LinearRamp_12b_RGB: result = Draw12BitRamp(); break;
2650  case NTV2_TestPatt_HLG_Narrow_12b_RGB: result = DrawTestPatternNarrowHLG(); break;
2651  case NTV2_TestPatt_PQ_Narrow_12b_RGB: result = DrawTestPatternNarrowPQ(); break;
2652  case NTV2_TestPatt_PQ_Wide_12b_RGB: result = DrawTestPatternWidePQ(); break;
2653  default: break; // unknown test pattern ID?
2654  }
2655  delete [] mpPackedLineBuffer;
2656  delete [] mpUnpackedLineBuffer;
2657  if (!result)
2658  {
2659  const NTV2TestPatternNames names(getTestPatternNames());
2660  if (mPatternID < names.size())
2661  TPGFAIL("Failed for pattern '" << names.at(mPatternID) << "'");
2662  else
2663  TPGFAIL("Failed for pattern " << DEC(mPatternID));
2664  }
2665  return result;
2666 } // drawIt
2667 
2668 #if !defined(NTV2_DEPRECATE_16_0)
2669  bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawTestPattern (const NTV2TestPatternSelect inPattern,
2670  const NTV2FormatDescriptor & inDesc,
2671  NTV2TestPatBuffer & outBuffer)
2672  {
2673  NTV2Buffer tmp(inDesc.GetTotalBytes());
2674  outBuffer.resize(0);
2675  return DrawTestPattern(inPattern, inDesc, tmp)
2676  && tmp.GetU8s (outBuffer, /*U8Offset*/0, /*MaxSize*/0);
2677  }
2678 
2679  bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawTestPattern (const NTV2TestPatternSelect inPattern,
2680  const uint32_t frameWidth,
2681  const uint32_t frameHeight,
2682  const NTV2FrameBufferFormat pixelFormat,
2683  NTV2TestPatBuffer & testPatternBuffer)
2684  {
2685  // Save this away for worker methods.
2686  mPatternID = inPattern;
2687  mDstFrameWidth = frameWidth;
2688  mDstFrameHeight = frameHeight;
2689  mDstPixelFormat = pixelFormat;
2690  mNumPixels = frameWidth;
2691 
2692  // HDR test pattern compatibility check
2693  if (NTV2_IS_12B_PATTERN(inPattern))
2694  { // HDR test pattern requested...
2695  if (mDstFrameWidth % 1920)
2696  {TPGFAIL("Pixel width " << DEC(mDstFrameWidth) << " not evenly divisible by 1920"); return false;}
2697  if (!NTV2_IS_FBF_12BIT_RGB(mDstPixelFormat))
2698  {TPGFAIL("Pixel format " << ::NTV2FrameBufferFormatToString(mDstPixelFormat) << " not 12-bit RGB"); return false;}
2699  }
2700 
2701  mDstLinePitch = ::CalcRowBytesForFormat(mDstPixelFormat, mDstFrameWidth); // BYTES per line of frame buffer format
2702  if (!mDstLinePitch)
2703  {TPGFAIL("CalcRowBytesForFormat failed for " << ::NTV2FrameBufferFormatToString(mDstPixelFormat) << " pxWidth=" << DEC(mDstFrameWidth)); return false;}
2704  mSrcLinePitch = ::CalcRowBytesForFormat(NTV2_FBF_10BIT_YCBCR, mDstFrameWidth); // BYTES per line of test pattern data (always stored as 10-bit YCbCr)
2705 
2706  mDstBufferSize = mDstLinePitch*mDstFrameHeight;
2707  if (!mDstBufferSize)
2708  {TPGFAIL("Buffer size zero, linePitch=" << DEC(mDstLinePitch) << " height=" << DEC(mDstFrameHeight)); return false;}
2709 
2710  if (testPatternBuffer.size() != mDstBufferSize)
2711  testPatternBuffer.resize(mDstBufferSize);
2712 
2713  mRGBBuffer.resize(frameWidth * frameHeight * 3 + 1);
2714  mpDstBuffer = &testPatternBuffer[0];
2715 
2716  mpPackedLineBuffer = new uint32_t[mDstFrameWidth*2];
2717  mpUnpackedLineBuffer = new uint16_t[mDstFrameWidth*4];
2718  MakeUnPacked10BitYCbCrBuffer(mpUnpackedLineBuffer,CCIR601_10BIT_BLACK,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,mDstFrameWidth);
2719  if (NTV2_IS_12B_PATTERN(inPattern))
2720  HDRTPGeometry geom(mNumPixels, mNumLines); // setupHDRTestPatternGeometries();
2721  return drawIt();
2722  } // DrawTestPattern
2723 #endif // !defined(NTV2_DEPRECATE_16_0)
2724 
2725 
2726 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawTestPattern (const NTV2TestPatternSelect inPattern,
2727  const NTV2FormatDescriptor & inFormatDesc,
2728  NTV2Buffer & buffer)
2729 {
2730  if (!NTV2_IS_VALID_PATTERN(inPattern))
2731  {TPGFAIL("Invalid pattern selector " << DEC(inPattern)); return false;}
2732  if (!buffer)
2733  {TPGFAIL("NULL buffer"); return false;}
2734  if (!inFormatDesc.IsValid())
2735  {TPGFAIL("Invalid format descriptor"); return false;}
2736  if (inFormatDesc.IsPlanar())
2737  {TPGFAIL("Planar format " << ::NTV2FrameBufferFormatToString(mDstPixelFormat) << " not implemented"); return false;}
2738 
2739  // Save this away for worker methods.
2740  mPatternID = inPattern;
2741  mDstFrameWidth = inFormatDesc.GetRasterWidth();
2742  mDstFrameHeight = inFormatDesc.GetVisibleRasterHeight();
2743  mDstPixelFormat = inFormatDesc.GetPixelFormat();
2744  mNumPixels = mDstFrameWidth;
2745 
2746  // HDR test pattern compatibility check
2747  if (NTV2_IS_12B_PATTERN(inPattern))
2748  { // HDR test pattern requested...
2749  if (mDstFrameWidth % 1920)
2750  {TPGFAIL("Pixel width " << DEC(mDstFrameWidth) << " not evenly divisible by 1920"); return false;}
2751  if (!NTV2_IS_FBF_12BIT_RGB(mDstPixelFormat))
2752  return false; // Pixel format must be RGB-12b
2753  }
2754 
2755  // BYTES per line of frame buffer format
2756  mDstLinePitch = inFormatDesc.GetBytesPerRow();
2757  if (!mDstLinePitch)
2758  {TPGFAIL("Zero line pitch for pattern " << DEC(inPattern)); return false;}
2759 
2760  // BYTES per line of test pattern data (always stored as 10-bit YCbCr)
2761  mSrcLinePitch = CalcRowBytesForFormat(NTV2_FBF_10BIT_YCBCR, mDstFrameWidth);
2762 
2763  mDstBufferSize = inFormatDesc.GetVisibleRasterBytes();
2764  if (!mDstBufferSize)
2765  {TPGFAIL("Buffer size is zero: " << inFormatDesc); return false;}
2766  if (mDstBufferSize != mDstLinePitch * mDstFrameHeight)
2767  {TPGFAIL("Buffer size " << DEC(mDstBufferSize) << " != " << DEC(mDstLinePitch*mDstFrameHeight) << " pitch=" << DEC(mDstLinePitch) << " * hght=" << DEC(mDstFrameHeight)); return false;}
2768 
2769  if (buffer.GetByteCount() < mDstBufferSize)
2770  {TPGFAIL("Actual buffer size " << DEC(buffer.GetByteCount()) << " < reqd size " << DEC(mDstBufferSize)); return false;}
2771 
2772  mRGBBuffer.resize(mDstFrameWidth * mDstFrameHeight * 3 + 1);
2773 
2774  mpDstBuffer = inFormatDesc.GetTopVisibleRowAddress(AsUBytePtr(buffer.GetHostPointer()));
2775 
2776  mpPackedLineBuffer = new uint32_t[mDstFrameWidth*2];
2777  mpUnpackedLineBuffer = new uint16_t[mDstFrameWidth*4];
2778  MakeUnPacked10BitYCbCrBuffer(mpUnpackedLineBuffer,CCIR601_10BIT_BLACK,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,mDstFrameWidth);
2779  if (NTV2_IS_12B_PATTERN(inPattern))
2780  HDRTPGeometry geom(mNumPixels, mNumLines); // setupHDRTestPatternGeometries();
2781 TPGDBUG("mpPackedLineBuff sz=" << DEC(mDstFrameWidth*2*4) << ", mpUnpackedLineBuff sz=" << DEC(mDstFrameWidth*4*2));
2782  bool ok(drawIt());
2783  if (ok && setVANCToLegalBlack() && inFormatDesc.IsVANC())
2784  { // Set the VANC area, if any, to legal black...
2785  if (!::SetRasterLinesBlack(inFormatDesc.GetPixelFormat(), AsUBytePtr(buffer.GetHostPointer()),
2786  UWord(inFormatDesc.GetBytesPerRow()), UWord(inFormatDesc.firstActiveLine)))
2787  TPGWARN("SetRasterLinesBlack failed for " << inFormatDesc);
2788  }
2789  return ok;
2790 } // DrawTestPattern
2791 
2792 
2793 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawTestPattern (const string & inStartsWith,
2794  const NTV2FormatDescriptor & inFormatDesc,
2795  NTV2Buffer & inBuffer)
2796 {
2797  string startsWith(inStartsWith);
2798  aja::strip(startsWith);
2799  if (startsWith.empty())
2800  {TPGFAIL("Empty 'startsWith' string"); return false;}
2801  if (!inBuffer)
2802  {TPGFAIL("NULL buffer"); return false;}
2803  if (!inFormatDesc.IsValid())
2804  {TPGFAIL("Invalid format descriptor"); return false;}
2805  if (inFormatDesc.IsPlanar())
2806  {TPGFAIL("Planar format " << ::NTV2FrameBufferFormatToString(mDstPixelFormat) << " not implemented"); return false;}
2807 
2808  // Try test pattern first...
2809  NTV2TestPatternSelect testPat(findTestPatternByName(startsWith));
2810  if (NTV2_IS_VALID_PATTERN(testPat))
2811  return DrawTestPattern(testPat, inFormatDesc, inBuffer);
2812 
2813  // Must be a web color...?
2814  ULWord rgbValue(findRGBColorByName(startsWith));
2815  if (!rgbValue)
2816  {TPGFAIL("No pattern or color that starts with '" << startsWith << "'"); return false;}
2817 
2818  // Save this away for worker methods.
2819  mPatternID = NTV2_TestPatt_INVALID;
2820  mDstFrameWidth = inFormatDesc.GetRasterWidth();
2821  mDstFrameHeight = inFormatDesc.GetVisibleRasterHeight();
2822  mDstPixelFormat = inFormatDesc.GetPixelFormat();
2823  mNumPixels = mDstFrameWidth;
2824 
2825  // BYTES per line of frame buffer format
2826  mDstLinePitch = inFormatDesc.GetBytesPerRow();
2827  if (!mDstLinePitch)
2828  {TPGFAIL("Line pitch is zero: " << inFormatDesc); return false;}
2829  const uint32_t tmpPitch(::CalcRowBytesForFormat(mDstPixelFormat, mDstFrameWidth));
2830  if (mDstLinePitch != tmpPitch)
2831  {TPGFAIL("Line pitch " << DEC(mDstLinePitch) << " from formatDesc doesn't match CalcRowBytesForFormat(" << DEC(mDstPixelFormat)
2832  << "," << DEC(mDstFrameWidth) << ") result: " << DEC(tmpPitch)); return false;}
2833 
2834  // BYTES per line of test pattern data (always stored as 10-bit YCbCr)
2835  mSrcLinePitch = ::CalcRowBytesForFormat(NTV2_FBF_10BIT_YCBCR, mDstFrameWidth);
2836 
2837  mDstBufferSize = inFormatDesc.GetVisibleRasterBytes();
2838  if (!mDstBufferSize)
2839  {TPGFAIL("Buffer size is zero: " << inFormatDesc); return false;}
2840  if (mDstBufferSize != mDstLinePitch * mDstFrameHeight)
2841  {TPGFAIL("Buffer size " << DEC(mDstBufferSize) << " != " << DEC(mDstLinePitch*mDstFrameHeight) << " pitch=" << DEC(mDstLinePitch) << " * hght=" << DEC(mDstFrameHeight)); return false;}
2842 
2843  if (inBuffer.GetByteCount() < mDstBufferSize)
2844  {TPGFAIL("Actual buffer size " << DEC(inBuffer.GetByteCount()) << " < reqd size " << DEC(mDstBufferSize)); return false;}
2845 
2846  mRGBBuffer.resize(mDstFrameWidth * mDstFrameHeight * 3 + 1);
2847  mpDstBuffer = inFormatDesc.GetTopVisibleRowAddress(AsUBytePtr(inBuffer.GetHostPointer()));
2848  mpPackedLineBuffer = new uint32_t[mDstFrameWidth*2];
2849  mpUnpackedLineBuffer = new uint16_t[mDstFrameWidth*4];
2850  MakeUnPacked10BitYCbCrBuffer(mpUnpackedLineBuffer,CCIR601_10BIT_BLACK,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,mDstFrameWidth);
2851 
2852  RGBAlphaPixel rgbaPixel; // Future: make this 12-bit?
2853  rgbaPixel.Alpha = 0;
2854  rgbaPixel.Red = (rgbValue & 0x00FF0000) >> 16;
2855  rgbaPixel.Green = (rgbValue & 0x0000FF00) >> 8;
2856  rgbaPixel.Blue = rgbValue & 0x000000FF;
2857  YCbCr10BitPixel yCbCrPixel;
2858  if (inFormatDesc.IsSD())
2859  SDConvertRGBAlphatoYCbCr(&rgbaPixel, &yCbCrPixel);
2860  else
2861  HDConvertRGBAlphatoYCbCr(&rgbaPixel, &yCbCrPixel);
2862  MakeUnPacked10BitYCbCrBuffer(mpUnpackedLineBuffer, yCbCrPixel.y, yCbCrPixel.cb, yCbCrPixel.cr, mDstFrameWidth);
2863  ConvertUnpacked10BitYCbCrToPixelFormat(mpUnpackedLineBuffer, mpPackedLineBuffer, mDstFrameWidth, mDstPixelFormat, mSetRGBSmpteRange, mSetAlphaFromLuma);
2864  for (uint32_t line(0); line < mDstFrameHeight; line++)
2865  {
2866  memcpy(mpDstBuffer, mpPackedLineBuffer, mDstLinePitch);
2867  mpDstBuffer += mDstLinePitch;
2868  }
2869  return true;
2870 } // DrawTestPattern
2871 
2872 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawSegmentedTestPattern()
2873 {
2874  bool is4K(false), is8K(false);
2875  int standard(0);
2876 
2877  // which video standard are we?
2878  if (!GetStandard(standard, is4K, is8K))
2879  return false;
2880 
2881  // find the appropriate test pattern descriptor
2882  const SegmentTestPatternData & testPatternSegmentData (NTV2TestPatternSegments[mPatternID]);
2883 
2884  // walk through the segments
2885  for (int segmentCount(0); segmentCount < NumTestPatternSegments; segmentCount++)
2886  {
2887  const SegmentDescriptor & segmentDescriptor (testPatternSegmentData.segmentDescriptor[standard][segmentCount]);
2888  const uint32_t * data = segmentDescriptor.data;
2889  if (!data)
2890  continue; // Try next segment
2891 
2892  // copy the test pattern line to the local "_pPackedLineBuffer"
2893  memcpy(mpPackedLineBuffer, data, mSrcLinePitch);
2894 
2895  if (mDstFrameWidth == HD_NUMCOMPONENTPIXELS_2K || mDstFrameWidth == HD_NUMCOMPONENTPIXELS_2K * 2 || mDstFrameWidth == HD_NUMCOMPONENTPIXELS_2K * 4)
2896  {
2897  UnPack10BitYCbCrBuffer(mpPackedLineBuffer, mpUnpackedLineBuffer, HD_NUMCOMPONENTPIXELS_1080);
2898  ReSampleYCbCrSampleLine(AsWordPtr(mpUnpackedLineBuffer), AsWordPtr(mpUnpackedLineBuffer), 1920, 2048);
2899  }
2900  else
2901  UnPack10BitYCbCrBuffer(mpPackedLineBuffer, mpUnpackedLineBuffer, mDstFrameWidth);
2902 
2903  int startLine = segmentDescriptor.startLine;
2904  int numLines = (segmentDescriptor.endLine - startLine) + 1;
2905 
2906  if (is4K)
2907  { // total kludge....just stretch out 1080 pattern.
2908  startLine *= 2;
2909  numLines *= 2;
2910 
2911  // stretch line by copying pixels.
2912  uint16_t* pLineSrc = &mpUnpackedLineBuffer[mDstFrameWidth-1];
2913  uint16_t* pLineDest = &mpUnpackedLineBuffer[mDstFrameWidth*2-1];
2914  for ( uint32_t count = 0; count < mDstFrameWidth/4; count ++)
2915  {
2916  uint16_t y2 = *pLineSrc--;
2917  uint16_t cr1 = *pLineSrc--;
2918  uint16_t y1 = *pLineSrc--;
2919  uint16_t cb1 = *pLineSrc--;
2920  *pLineDest-- = y2;
2921  *pLineDest-- = cr1;
2922  *pLineDest-- = y1;
2923  *pLineDest-- = cb1;
2924  *pLineDest-- = y2;
2925  *pLineDest-- = cr1;
2926  *pLineDest-- = y1;
2927  *pLineDest-- = cb1;
2928 
2929  }
2930  }
2931 
2932  if (is8K)
2933  { // total kludge....just stretch out 1080 pattern.
2934  startLine *= 4;
2935  numLines *= 4;
2936 
2937  // stretch line by copying pixels.
2938  uint16_t* pLineSrc = &mpUnpackedLineBuffer[mDstFrameWidth - 1];
2939  uint16_t* pLineDest = &mpUnpackedLineBuffer[mDstFrameWidth * 4 - 1];
2940  for (uint32_t count = 0; count < mDstFrameWidth / 4; count++)
2941  {
2942  uint16_t y2 = *pLineSrc--;
2943  uint16_t cr1 = *pLineSrc--;
2944  uint16_t y1 = *pLineSrc--;
2945  uint16_t cb1 = *pLineSrc--;
2946  *pLineDest-- = y2;
2947  *pLineDest-- = cr1;
2948  *pLineDest-- = y1;
2949  *pLineDest-- = cb1;
2950  *pLineDest-- = y2;
2951  *pLineDest-- = cr1;
2952  *pLineDest-- = y1;
2953  *pLineDest-- = cb1;
2954  *pLineDest-- = y2;
2955  *pLineDest-- = cr1;
2956  *pLineDest-- = y1;
2957  *pLineDest-- = cb1;
2958  *pLineDest-- = y2;
2959  *pLineDest-- = cr1;
2960  *pLineDest-- = y1;
2961  *pLineDest-- = cb1;
2962 
2963  }
2964  }
2965 
2966  // go through hoops to mask out undesired components
2967  if (mPatternID == NTV2_TestPatt_MultiBurst || mPatternID == NTV2_TestPatt_LineSweep )// || _patternNumber == NTV2_TestPatt_Ramp)
2968  {
2969  mSignalMask = NTV2_SIGNALMASK_Y; // just assume that Multiburst and LineSweep are "Y Only"
2970  MaskUnPacked10BitYCbCrBuffer(mpUnpackedLineBuffer, uint16_t(mSignalMask), mDstFrameWidth);
2971  }
2972 
2973  // now RE-pack, according to the desired pixel format
2974  ConvertUnpacked10BitYCbCrToPixelFormat(mpUnpackedLineBuffer, mpPackedLineBuffer, mDstFrameWidth, mDstPixelFormat, mSetRGBSmpteRange, mSetAlphaFromLuma);
2975 
2976  // calculate address of first line of segment in destination frame buffer
2977  uint8_t *pBuffer = mpDstBuffer + (uint32_t(startLine) * mDstLinePitch);
2978 
2979  // copy and repeat for as many lines as called for in segment
2980  for (int line(0); line < numLines; line++)
2981  {
2982  memcpy(pBuffer, mpPackedLineBuffer, mDstLinePitch);
2983  pBuffer += mDstLinePitch;
2984  }
2985  } // for each segment
2986 
2987  return true;
2988 } // DrawSegmentedTestPattern

3051 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawBorderFrame()
3052 {

3057

3059  MakeUnPacked10BitYCbCrBuffer(pUnPackedWhiteBuffer,CCIR601_10BIT_WHITE,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET,mDstFrameWidth);

3065  pUnPackedEdgeBuffer[(mDstFrameWidth)*2-1] = CCIR601_10BIT_WHITE;
3066  pUnPackedEdgeBuffer[(mDstFrameWidth)*2-2] = CCIR601_10BIT_CHROMAOFFSET;
3067

3074  ::memcpy(mpDstBuffer,pPackedWhiteLineBuffer,mDstLinePitch);
3075  else

3077

3079  }
3080

3083  delete [] pUnPackedEdgeBuffer;
3084  delete [] pUnPackedWhiteBuffer;

3088 static uint16_t MakeSineWaveVideoEx (const double radians, const bool bChroma, const double Gain)
3089 {
3090  // 10-bit YUV values
3091  static const int kYUVBlack10 (64);
3092  static const int kYUVWhite10 (940);
3093  static const int kYUVMinChroma10 (64);
3094  static const int kYUVMaxChroma10 (960);
3095 
3096  uint16_t result(0);
3097  double Scale(0.0);
3098  double Offset(0.0);
3099 
3100  if (!bChroma)
3101  {
3102  Scale = (double(kYUVWhite10) - double(kYUVBlack10)) / 2.0;
3103  Offset = (double(kYUVWhite10) + double(kYUVBlack10)) / 2.0;
3104 
3105  // calculate -cosine value to start Y at minimum value
3106  result = uint16_t((sin(radians) * Scale * Gain) + Offset + 0.5); // convert to 10-bit luma video levels
3107  }
3108  else
3109  {
3110  Scale = (double(kYUVMaxChroma10) - double(kYUVMinChroma10)) / 2.0;
3111  Offset = (double(kYUVMaxChroma10) + double(kYUVMinChroma10)) / 2.0;
3112 
3113  // calculate sine value to start C at "zero" value
3114  result = uint16_t((sin(radians) * Scale * Gain) + Offset + 0.5); // convert to 10-bit chroma video levels
3115  }
3116  return result;
3117 }
3118 
3119 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawZonePlateFrame()
3120 {
3121  static const double kPi(3.1415926535898);
3122  double pattScale = (kPi*.5 ) / (mDstFrameWidth + 1);
3123 
3124  for (uint32_t line(0); line < mDstFrameHeight; line++)
3125  {
3126  for (uint16_t pixel(0); pixel < mDstFrameWidth; pixel++)
3127  {
3128  double xDist = double(pixel) - (double(mDstFrameWidth) / 2.0);
3129  double yDist = double(line) - (double(mDstFrameHeight) / 2.0);
3130  double r = ((xDist * xDist) + (yDist * yDist)) * pattScale;
3131 
3132  mpUnpackedLineBuffer[pixel*2+1] = MakeSineWaveVideoEx(r, false, mSliderValue);
3133  mpUnpackedLineBuffer[pixel*2 ] = MakeSineWaveVideoEx(r, true, mSliderValue);
3134 
3135  }
3136  ConvertUnpacked10BitYCbCrToPixelFormat(mpUnpackedLineBuffer, mpPackedLineBuffer,mDstFrameWidth,mDstPixelFormat,mSetRGBSmpteRange, mSetAlphaFromLuma);
3137  ::memcpy(mpDstBuffer,mpPackedLineBuffer,mDstLinePitch);
3138  mpDstBuffer += mDstLinePitch;
3139  }
3140  return true;
3141 }

3373  mpDstBuffer += mDstLinePitch;
3374 
3375  ::memcpy(mpDstBuffer, pPackedLowerLineBuffer, mDstLinePitch);
3376  mpDstBuffer += mDstLinePitch;
3377  }
3378 
3379  delete [] pUnPackedUpperLineBuffer;
3380  delete [] pPackedUpperLineBuffer;
3381  delete [] pUnPackedLowerLineBuffer;
3382  delete [] pPackedLowerLineBuffer;
3383  return true;
3384 }

3386 
3387 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawColorQuadrantFrameTsi2()
3388 {
3389  const uint32_t innerDim = mDstFrameHeight / 12;
3390  const uint32_t outerDim = mDstFrameHeight / 6;
3391  const uint32_t lineWidth = 3;
3392 
3393  uint32_t unpackBufferSize = mDstFrameWidth * 4; // for each pixel: 2 components * 2 bytes per component
3394  uint16_t* pUnPackedWhiteBuffer= new uint16_t[unpackBufferSize];
3395  uint16_t* pUnPackedLineInBuffer= new uint16_t[unpackBufferSize];
3396  uint16_t* pUnPackedLineOutBuffer= new uint16_t[unpackBufferSize];
3397  uint16_t* pUnPackedPillarInBuffer= new uint16_t[unpackBufferSize];
3398  uint16_t* pUnPackedPillarInOutBuffer= new uint16_t[unpackBufferSize];
3399  uint16_t* pUnPackedTempBuffer= new uint16_t[unpackBufferSize];
3400  uint32_t* pPackedTempBuffer = new uint32_t[unpackBufferSize];
3401 
3402  YCbCr10BitPixel yCbCrPixelBlack;
3403  YCbCr10BitPixel yCbCrPixelWhite;
3404 
3405  // Colors for the quadrants are from SMPTE 435-1-2009 section 6.4.2
3406  static const unsigned char fullRange = 235;
3407 
3408  RGBAlphaPixel rgbaPixel;
3409  rgbaPixel.Alpha = 0; // white
3410  rgbaPixel.Red = fullRange;
3411  rgbaPixel.Green = fullRange;
3412  rgbaPixel.Blue = fullRange;
3413  HDConvertRGBAlphatoYCbCr(&rgbaPixel, &yCbCrPixelWhite);
3414 
3415  rgbaPixel.Alpha = 0; // black
3416  rgbaPixel.Red = 0;
3417  rgbaPixel.Green = 0;
3418  rgbaPixel.Blue = 0;
3419  HDConvertRGBAlphatoYCbCr(&rgbaPixel, &yCbCrPixelBlack);
3420 
3421  // square line params
3422  uint32_t centerH = mDstFrameWidth / 2;
3423  uint32_t centerV = mDstFrameHeight / 2;
3424 
3425  uint32_t innerLeft = centerH - innerDim;
3426  uint32_t innerRight = centerH + innerDim;
3427  uint32_t outerLeft = centerH - outerDim;
3428  uint32_t outerRight = centerH + outerDim;
3429 
3430  uint32_t innerTop = centerV - innerDim;
3431  uint32_t innerBot = centerV + innerDim;
3432  uint32_t outerTop = centerV - outerDim;
3433  uint32_t outerBot = centerV + outerDim;
3434 
3435  // white line
3436  uint32_t h;
3437  uint16_t *ptr;
3438  for (h = 0, ptr = pUnPackedWhiteBuffer; h < mDstFrameWidth; h++)
3439  {
3440  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.cb;
3441  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.y;
3442  }
3443 
3444  // black inner horizontal line
3445  for (h = 0, ptr = pUnPackedLineInBuffer; h < innerLeft; h++)
3446  {
3447  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.cb;
3448  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.y;
3449  }
3450  for (; h < innerRight; h++)
3451  {
3452  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelBlack.cb;
3453  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelBlack.y;
3454  }
3455  for (; h < mDstFrameWidth; h++)
3456  {
3457  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.cb;
3458  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.y;
3459  }
3460 
3461  // black outer horizontal line
3462  for (h = 0, ptr = pUnPackedLineOutBuffer; h < outerLeft; h++)
3463  {
3464  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.cb;
3465  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.y;
3466  }
3467  for (; h < outerRight; h++)
3468  {
3469  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelBlack.cb;
3470  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelBlack.y;
3471  }
3472  for (; h < mDstFrameWidth; h++)
3473  {
3474  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.cb;
3475  *ptr++ = yCbCrPixelWhite.y;
3476  }
3477 
3478  // pillar inner lines
3479  ::memcpy(pUnPackedPillarInBuffer, pUnPackedWhiteBuffer, unpackBufferSize);
3480  for (h=innerLeft; h < innerLeft + lineWidth; h++) // overwrite
3481  {
3482  pUnPackedPillarInBuffer[h*2] = yCbCrPixelBlack.cb;
3483  pUnPackedPillarInBuffer[h*2 + 1] = yCbCrPixelBlack.y;
3484  }
3485  for (h=innerRight - lineWidth; h < innerRight; h++) // overwrite
3486  {
3487  pUnPackedPillarInBuffer[h*2] = yCbCrPixelBlack.cb;
3488  pUnPackedPillarInBuffer[h*2 + 1] = yCbCrPixelBlack.y;
3489  }
3490 
3491  // pillar outer/inner lines - start with inner lines
3492  ::memcpy(pUnPackedPillarInOutBuffer, pUnPackedPillarInBuffer, unpackBufferSize);
3493  for (h=outerLeft; h < outerLeft + lineWidth; h++) // overwrite
3494  {
3495  pUnPackedPillarInOutBuffer[h*2] = yCbCrPixelBlack.cb;
3496  pUnPackedPillarInOutBuffer[h*2 + 1] = yCbCrPixelBlack.y;
3497  }
3498  for (h=outerRight - lineWidth; h < outerRight; h++) // overwrite
3499  {
3500  pUnPackedPillarInOutBuffer[h*2] = yCbCrPixelBlack.cb;
3501  pUnPackedPillarInOutBuffer[h*2 + 1] = yCbCrPixelBlack.y;
3502  }
3503 
3504  // image top
3505  uint32_t marginWidth = (mDstFrameWidth - mDstFrameHeight) / 2;
3506  uint32_t diagLeftIdx = marginWidth * 2;
3507  uint32_t diagRightIdx = (mDstFrameWidth - marginWidth) * 2;
3508 
3509  for (uint32_t v(0); v < mDstFrameHeight; v ++)
3510  {
3511  // fill in background line for center square
3512  if (v < outerTop)
3513  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedWhiteBuffer, unpackBufferSize); // white
3514  else if (v < outerTop+lineWidth)
3515  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedLineInBuffer, unpackBufferSize); // line top
3516  else if (v < innerTop)
3517  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedPillarInBuffer, unpackBufferSize); // pillar
3518  else if (v < innerTop+lineWidth)
3519  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedLineOutBuffer, unpackBufferSize); // long-line top
3520  else if (v < innerBot-lineWidth)
3521  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedPillarInOutBuffer, unpackBufferSize);// double pillar
3522  else if (v < innerBot)
3523  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedLineOutBuffer, unpackBufferSize); // long-line bot
3524  else if (v < outerBot-lineWidth)
3525  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedPillarInBuffer, unpackBufferSize); // pillar
3526  else if (v < outerBot)
3527  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedLineInBuffer, unpackBufferSize); // line bot
3528  else
3529  ::memcpy(pUnPackedTempBuffer, pUnPackedWhiteBuffer, unpackBufferSize); // white
3530 
3531  // overlay one-pixel diagonal cross
3532  pUnPackedTempBuffer[diagLeftIdx++] = yCbCrPixelBlack.cb;
3533  pUnPackedTempBuffer[diagLeftIdx++] = yCbCrPixelBlack.y;
3534  pUnPackedTempBuffer[diagRightIdx--] = yCbCrPixelBlack.cb;
3535  pUnPackedTempBuffer[diagRightIdx--] = yCbCrPixelBlack.y;
3536 
3537  // copy to output buffer
3538  ConvertUnpacked10BitYCbCrToPixelFormat(pUnPackedTempBuffer, (uint32_t*)pPackedTempBuffer, mDstFrameWidth, mDstPixelFormat);
3539  memcpy(mpDstBuffer, pPackedTempBuffer, mDstLinePitch);
3540  mpDstBuffer += mDstLinePitch;
3541  }
3542 
3543  delete [] pUnPackedWhiteBuffer;
3544  delete [] pUnPackedLineInBuffer;
3545  delete [] pUnPackedLineOutBuffer;
3546  delete [] pUnPackedPillarInBuffer;
3547  delete [] pUnPackedPillarInOutBuffer;
3548  delete [] pUnPackedTempBuffer;
3549  delete [] pPackedTempBuffer;
3550  return true;
3551 }

3553 
3554 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::GetStandard (int & outStandard, bool & outIs4K, bool & outIs8K) const
3555 {
3556  outIs4K = outIs8K = false;
3557 
3558  if (mDstFrameWidth == 1920)
3559  outStandard = int(NTV2_STANDARD_1080);
3560 
3561  else if (mDstFrameWidth == 2048)
3562  outStandard = int(NTV2_STANDARD_1080);
3563 
3564  else if (mDstFrameWidth == 1280)
3565  outStandard = int(NTV2_STANDARD_720);
3566 
3567  else if (mDstFrameWidth == 720 && mDstFrameHeight == 486)
3568  outStandard = int(NTV2_STANDARD_525);
3569 
3570  else if (mDstFrameWidth == 720 && mDstFrameHeight == 576)
3571  outStandard = int(NTV2_STANDARD_625);
3572 
3573  else if (mDstFrameWidth == 2048 && mDstFrameHeight == 1556)
3574  outStandard = int(NTV2_STANDARD_2K); // Obsolete
3575 
3576  else if ((mDstFrameWidth == 3840 && mDstFrameHeight == 2160) ||
3577  (mDstFrameWidth == 4096 && mDstFrameHeight == 2160))
3578  {
3579  outStandard = int(NTV2_STANDARD_1080);
3580  outIs4K = true;
3581  }
3582  else if ((mDstFrameWidth == 7680 && mDstFrameHeight == 4320) ||
3583  (mDstFrameWidth == 8192 && mDstFrameHeight == 4320))
3584  {
3585  outStandard = int(NTV2_STANDARD_1080);
3586  outIs8K = true;
3587  }
3588 
3589  else
3590  return false;
3591  return true;
3592 }
3593 
3594 
3595 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::IsSDStandard(void) const
3596 {
3597  int standard;
3598  bool b4K, b8K;
3599  if (GetStandard(standard, b4K, b8K))
3600  return (standard == 2 || standard == 3);
3601  return false;
3602 }

3604 static AJA_RGB16BitPixel* addToBuffer (AJA_RGB16BitPixel* buffer, const AJA_RGB16BitPixel & value, const uint32_t length)
3605 {
3606  for (uint32_t i(0); i < length; i++)
3607  *buffer++ = value;
3608  return buffer;
3609 }
3610 
3611 static AJA_RGB16BitPixel* addRampToBuffer (AJA_RGB16BitPixel* buffer, const AJA_RGB16BitPixel& value, const uint32_t length, const uint32_t incrementValue)
3612 {
3613  AJA_RGB16BitPixel pixel(value);
3614 
3615  for (uint32_t i(0); i < length; i++)
3616  {
3617  *buffer++ = pixel;
3618  pixel.Red += incrementValue;
3619  pixel.Green += incrementValue;
3620  pixel.Blue += incrementValue;
3621 
3622  }
3623  return buffer;
3624 }
3625 
3626 static void ConvertRGBLineTo10BitYCbCr422 (AJA_RGB16BitPixel* lineBuffer, const uint32_t lineLength)
3627 {
3628  int16_t r,g,b;
3629  int16_t y,cb,cr;
3630 //ostringstream dbg;
3631  r =0;
3632  g = 512;
3633  b = 1023;
3634 
3635  y = int16_t((r-64.0)*(.26270) + (g-64.0)*(.67800) + (b-64)*(.05930) + 64.0);
3636  cb = int16_t((r-64.0)*(-0.14282) + (g-64.0)*(-0.368594) + (b-64.0)*(0.511414) + 512.0);
3637  cr = int16_t((r-64.0)*(0.511414) + (g-64.0)*(-0.470284) + (b-64.0)*(-0.04113) + 512.0);
3638  //dbg << endl << "Y=" << y << " Cb=" << cb << " Cr=" << cr << endl;
3639 
3640  for (uint32_t pixel(0); pixel < lineLength; pixel++)
3641  {
3642  AJA_RGB16BitPixel pixelValue = lineBuffer[pixel];
3643  //Make 10 bit Value
3644  r = pixelValue.Red >> 2;
3645  g = pixelValue.Green >> 2;
3646  b = pixelValue.Blue >> 2;
3647  y = int16_t((r-64.0)*( 0.262700) + (g-64.0)*( 0.678000) + (b-64.0)*( 0.059300) + 64.0);
3648  cb = int16_t((r-64.0)*(-0.142820) + (g-64.0)*(-0.368594) + (b-64.0)*( 0.511414) + 512.0);
3649  cr = int16_t((r-64.0)*( 0.511414) + (g-64.0)*(-0.470284) + (b-64.0)*(-0.041130) + 512.0);
3650  if ( y > 1020) y = 1020;
3651  if ( y < 4) y = 4;
3652  if (cb > 1020) cb = 1020;
3653  if (cb < 4) cb = 4;
3654  if (cr > 1020) cr = 1020;
3655  if (cr < 4) cr = 4;
3656  #if 0
3657  if (pixel & 0x1)
3658  dbg << DEC(y) << ",";
3659  else
3660  dbg << DEC(cb) << ',' << DEC(y) << ',' << DEC(cr) << ',';
3661  if (pixel && !(pixel%16))
3662  oss << endl;
3663  #endif
3664  }
3665 //cout << dbg.str() << endl;
3666 }
3667 
3668 void NTV2TestPatternGen::PrepareForOutput()
3669 {
3670  if (mDstPixelFormat == NTV2_FBF_12BIT_RGB_PACKED)
3671  {
3672  // Not sure why we don't just cache the mDstFormatDesc??
3673  size_t tmpBufSize = mNumPixels * mNumLines * 18; // memory format is w * h * 36px / 8px * 4 bytes;
3674  NTV2Buffer tmpBuf (tmpBufSize);
3675  uint16_t* pSrc16 = mRGBBuffer.data();
3676  uint8_t* pTmp8 = tmpBuf;
3677  for (uint32_t y = 0; y < mNumLines; y++) {
3678  int loops = mNumPixels/2;
3679  int srcAdv = 6; // 6 bytes * 2px
3680  int dstAdv = 9; // 9 bytes per 2px
3681  for (int i = 0; i < loops; i++) {
3682  uint16_t r1 = pSrc16[0];
3683  uint16_t g1 = pSrc16[1];
3684  uint16_t b1 = pSrc16[2];
3685  uint16_t r2 = pSrc16[3];
3686  uint16_t g2 = pSrc16[4];
3687  uint16_t b2 = pSrc16[5];
3688  pTmp8[0] = (r1 & 0xFF0) >> 4;
3689  pTmp8[1] = ((r1 & 0x00F) << 4) + ((g1 & 0xF00) >> 8);
3690  pTmp8[2] = (g1 & 0x0FF);
3691  pTmp8[3] = ((b1 & 0xFF0) >> 4);
3692  pTmp8[4] = ((b1 & 0x00F) << 4) + ((r2 & 0xF00) >> 8);
3693  pTmp8[5] = (r2 & 0x0FF);
3694  pTmp8[6] = ((g2 & 0xFF0) >> 4);
3695  pTmp8[7] = ((g2 & 0x00F) << 4) + ((b2 & 0xF00) >> 8);
3696  pTmp8[8] = (b2 & 0x0FF);
3697  pSrc16 += srcAdv;
3698  pTmp8 += dstAdv;
3699  }
3700  }
3701  ::memcpy(mpDstBuffer, AsUInt8Ptr(tmpBuf.GetHostPointer()), mDstBufferSize);
3702  }
3703  else
3704  {
3705  NTV2Buffer tmpBuffer (mNumPixels * mNumLines * 3 * sizeof(uint16_t));
3706  uint16_t* rgb16BitBuffer = tmpBuffer;
3707  uint16_t* rgb12Buffer = mRGBBuffer.data();
3708  ULWord* buffer = AsULWordPtr(rgb16BitBuffer);
3709  for (uint32_t i(0); i < mNumPixels*mNumLines; i++)
3710  {
3711  uint16_t r = uint16_t((*rgb12Buffer++) << 4);
3712  uint16_t g = uint16_t((*rgb12Buffer++) << 4);
3713  uint16_t b = uint16_t((*rgb12Buffer++) << 4);
3714  *rgb16BitBuffer++ = b; // b
3715  *rgb16BitBuffer++ = g; //g
3716  *rgb16BitBuffer++ = r;
3717  }
3718  ::memcpy(mpDstBuffer, AsUInt8Ptr(buffer), mDstBufferSize);
3719  }
3720 }
3721

3723 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawTestPatternNarrowHLG()

3743

3746  {
3747  memcpy(rgbBuffer,tempBuffer,geom.a*sizeof(AJA_RGB16BitPixel));
3748  rgbBuffer += geom.a;
3749 
3750  }

3760  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowBlue75, geom.d);

3762

3764  {

3766  rgbBuffer += geom.a;
3767 
3768  }
3769 
3770  // build line of 3rd segment
3771  lineBuffer = tempBuffer;
3772  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowWhite75, geom.c);
3773  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowStepMinus7, geom.d);

3775  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowStep10, geom.d/2);

3785  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowStep109, geom.d/2);
3786  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowWhite75, geom.c);
3787

3791  rgbBuffer += geom.a;

3800

3802  {
3803  memcpy(rgbBuffer, tempBuffer, geom.a*sizeof(AJA_RGB16BitPixel));
3804  rgbBuffer += geom.a;

3808  lineBuffer = tempBuffer;

3814  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowBlack, geom.h);

3835 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::DrawTestPatternNarrowPQ()
3836 {
3837  mBitsPerComponent = 16;
3838  const HDRTPGeometry geom(mNumPixels, mNumLines);
3839 
3840  AJA_RGB16BitPixel* rgbBuffer = AsRGB16Ptr(mRGBBuffer.data());
3841 
3842  AJA_RGB16BitPixel* tempBuffer = new AJA_RGB16BitPixel[geom.a*2];
3843  AJA_RGB16BitPixel* lineBuffer = tempBuffer;
3844 
3845  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowGrey40, geom.c);
3846  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowWhite100, geom.d);
3847  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowYellow100, geom.d);
3848  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowCyan100, geom.d);
3849  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowGreen100, geom.d);
3850  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowMagenta100, geom.d);
3851  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowRed100, geom.d);
3852  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowBlue100, geom.d);
3853  lineBuffer = addToBuffer(lineBuffer, NarrowGrey40, geom.c);
3854  ConvertRGBLineTo10BitYCbCr422(tempBuffer, mNumPixels);
3855  //qDebug() << "between the lines";
3856

4060 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::Draw12BitRamp()
4061 {
4062  mBitsPerComponent = 16;
4063  size_t ndx(0);//uint16_t* rgbBuffer (&mRGBBuffer.at(0));
4064  NTV2_ASSERT(mRGBBuffer.size() >= size_t(3*mNumPixels*mNumLines));
4065  for (uint32_t lineCount(0); lineCount < mNumLines; lineCount++)
4066  for (uint32_t pixelCount(0); pixelCount < mNumPixels; pixelCount++)
4067  {
4068  const double dvalue (double(pixelCount)*(4095.0/double(mNumPixels-1)));
4069  const uint16_t ivalue = uint16_t(dvalue);
4070  mRGBBuffer.at(ndx++) = ivalue;
4071  mRGBBuffer.at(ndx++) = ivalue;
4072  mRGBBuffer.at(ndx++) = ivalue;
4073  }
4074  PrepareForOutput();
4075  return true;
4076 }
4077 
4078 
4079 static const int kRGBMinChroma12 (0x10);
4080 static const int kRGBMaxChroma12 (0xFEF);
4081 static const double kRGBSpanChroma12 (double(kRGBMaxChroma12) - double(kRGBMinChroma12));
4082 static const double kRGBTotalChroma12 (double(kRGBMaxChroma12) + double(kRGBMinChroma12));
4083 static const double kPi(3.1415926535898);
4084 //const int kYUVZeroChroma10 = 512;
4085 
4086 static uint32_t MakeSineWaveVideo (const double radians, const double Gain)
4087 {
4088  const double Scale(kRGBSpanChroma12 / 2.0), Offset(kRGBTotalChroma12 / 2.0);
4089  // calculate sine value to start C at "zero" value
4090  return uint32_t((sin(radians) * Scale * Gain) + Offset + 0.5); // convert to 12-bit chroma video levels
4091 }
4092 
4093 bool NTV2TestPatternGen::Draw12BitZonePlate()
4094 {
4095  mBitsPerComponent = 16;
4096  const double pattScale ((kPi * 0.5 ) / double(mNumPixels + 1));
4097  size_t ndx(0);//uint16_t * pRGBBuffer (&mRGBBuffer.at(0));
4098  NTV2_ASSERT(mRGBBuffer.size() >= size_t(3*mNumPixels*mNumLines));
4099  for (uint32_t lineCount(0); lineCount < mNumLines; lineCount++)
4100  for (uint32_t pixelCount(0); pixelCount < mNumPixels; pixelCount++)
4101  {
4102  const double xDist(double(pixelCount) - (double(mNumPixels) / 2.0));
4103  const double yDist(double(lineCount) - (double(mNumLines) / 2.0));
4104  const double r (((xDist * xDist) + (yDist * yDist)) * pattScale);
4105  const uint16_t u16 (uint16_t(MakeSineWaveVideo(r, 0.9)));
4106 
4107  mRGBBuffer[ndx++] = u16;
4108  mRGBBuffer[ndx++] = u16;
4109  mRGBBuffer[ndx++] = u16;
4110  }
4111  PrepareForOutput();
4112  return true;
4113 }
